{"lemma":"دُفْعَةُ","slug":"دُفْعَةُ","root":"د.ف.ع","root_slug":"د-ف-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ف-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adv","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12714","n12720","n12721"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a push, a thrust","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one go","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a graduating class, a school class, a batch","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a payment","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"in one go, in one foul swoop"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun from دَفَعَ (dafaʕa, “to push”).\n\nInstance noun from دَفَعَ (dafaʕa, “to push, to pay”).\n\nAdverbial accusative of دَفْعَة (dafʕa)."},"ipa":["/daf.ʕa/","/duf.ʕa/","/daf.ʕa.tan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12714","headword_ar":"دَفَعَهُ","root":"dfE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafoEN","text_ar":"دَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaAEN","text_ar":"دَفَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madofaEN","text_ar":"مَدْفَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He impelled it, pushed it, thrust it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drove it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to remove it from its place; he propelled it; he repelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repulsed, it; he pushed it, thrust it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drove it, away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put it away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed it from its place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with, force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafoEN","text_ar":"دَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"putting away"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning back"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before the coming"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arriving"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of that thing]; like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafoEN","text_ar":"رَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the “ putting away or removing or turning back ” a thing “ after the coming or arriving ” thereof. (Kull p. 185.) Hence the saying in the Kur [ii. 252, and xxii. 41],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walawo laA dafoEu A@ll~`hi Aln~aAsa","text_ar":"وَلَوْ لَا دَفْعُ ا@للّٰهِ النَّاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And were it not for God's repelling men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; where some read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difaAEu","text_ar":"دِفَاعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means the same, as will be seen in the course of what follows, though bearing also another interpretation, likewise to be seen in what follows]. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajula","text_ar":"الرَّجُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I impelled, pushed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the man"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dAfEhu","text_ar":"دافعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difaAEN","text_ar":"دِفَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudaAfaEapN","text_ar":"مُدَافَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"df~Ehu","text_ar":"دفّعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [both, app., accord. to the TA, signifying the same; but the latter more properly relates to several objects together, or signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he impelled it, pushed it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereas]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudaAfaEapN","text_ar":"مُدَافَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difaAEN","text_ar":"دِفَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) are [often exactly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafoEN","text_ar":"دَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) Thus, (TA,) you say, as meaning the same,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dAfE","text_ar":"دافع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa","text_ar":"دَفَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repelled from him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence another explanation of these two phrases, which see in what follows]. (S, TA.) And hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa A@ll~`hu Eanoka Almakoruwha","text_ar":"دَفَعَ ا@للّٰهُ عَنْكَ المَكْرُوهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafoEN","text_ar":"دَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God repel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avert, from thee what is disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu Eanoka Als~uwo'a","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ عَنْكَ السُّوْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAfaEa","text_ar":"دَافَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difaAEN","text_ar":"دِفَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God repel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avert, from thee evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu Eanohu AlA^a*aY","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ عَنْهُ الاَذَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I repelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"averted, from him what was hurtful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"annoying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAfaEotu","text_ar":"دَافَعْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb, K, TA.) Sb mentions, as a saying of the Arabs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AidofaEi Al$~ar~a","text_ar":"اِدْفَعِ الشَّرَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walawo A_iSobaEFA","text_ar":"وَلَوْ اـِصْبَعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Repel thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avert thou, evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief, though but with a finger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the last word being in the accus. case by reason of the subaudition of the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the meaning being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA_iSobaEK","text_ar":"بِاـِصْبَعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafuwEN","text_ar":"دَفُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafoEN","text_ar":"دَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and has a single objective complement, a second objective complement is understood, and in general] it has the meaning or the act of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Defending;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur [xxii. 39],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a A@ll~`ha yadofaEu Eano A@l~a*iyna A=manuwA","text_ar":"اـِنَّ ا@للّٰهَ يَدْفَعُ عَنْ ا@لَّذِينَ ا=مَنُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily God defendeth those who have believed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repelleth from them"},{"kind":"text","text":"aggression and the like]; (B;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yudaAfiEu","text_ar":"يُدَافِعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the same, (K, TA,) accord. to another reading, signifies the same; (K, TA;) or this latter signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defendeth energetically, with the energy of him who contendeth for superiority in so doing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAfaEotu","text_ar":"دَافَعْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [also] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I pleaded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contended in arguments, in defence of him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [Exceptions to the statement cited above form the B will be found in what follows in this paragraph; and another exception, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudaf~aEN","text_ar":"مُدَفَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [In the exs. which follow, the verb is used in senses little differing, essentially, from those assigned to it in the first sentence of this art.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu mina AlA_inaA='i","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ مِنَ الاـِنَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafoaEapF","text_ar":"دَفَْعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I poured forth from the vessel a single pouring"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the last word, which is with fet-h, is an inf. n. [of un.]. (Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEati All~ibaA^afiY","text_ar":"دَفَعَتِ اللِّبَاَفِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaroEihaA qubayola Aln~itaAji","text_ar":"ضَرْعِهَا قُبَيْلَ النِّتَاجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a ewe, or goat, S, or a camel, S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"infused the first milk into her udder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secreted it therein, a little before bringing forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEati All~abani EalaY","text_ar":"دَفَعَتِ اللَّبَنِ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osi waladihaA likavoratihi","text_ar":"رَاْسِ وَلَدِهَا لِكَثْرَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a ewe or goat, or a camel, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secreted the milk in her udder when about to produce her young, by reason of its abundance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; for the milk becomes abundant in her udder only when she is about to bring forth: the inf. n. [app. the inf. n. of un.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafoEapN","text_ar":"دَفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEato","text_ar":"دَفَعَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, said of a ewe or goat, signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She secreted milk in her udder when about to produce the young;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoraEato EalaY raA^osi","text_ar":"اَضْرَعَتْ عَلَى رَاْسِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwaladi","text_ar":"الوَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DrE","text_ar":"ضرع"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) Accord. to En-Nadr, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEato bilabinihaA","text_ar":"دَفَعَتْ بِلَبِنِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAll~abani","text_ar":"بِاللَّبَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", when her young is in her belly; but when she has brought forth, one does not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEato","text_ar":"دَفَعَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  In the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ga$iyitonaA saHaAbapN fadafaEonaAhaA A_ilaY gayorinaA","text_ar":"غَشِيِتْنَا سَحَابَةٌ فَدَفَعْنَاهَا اـِلَى غَيْرِنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cloud overspread us, and we drove it away to other persons"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it departed from us to other persons,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dfEnAhA","text_ar":"دفعناها"},{"kind":"text","text":"is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEatonaA","text_ar":"دَفَعَتْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dufiEato Ean~aA","text_ar":"دُفِعَتْ عَنَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was driven away from us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEahu biHuj~apK","text_ar":"دَفَعَهُ بِحُجَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He refelled him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuted him, by an argument"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (MF in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kfH","text_ar":"كفح"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu Alqawola","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ القَوْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rebutted the saying; repelled it by an argument, an allegation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a proof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AidofaEo h`*aA","text_ar":"اِدْفَعْ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou this, sparing him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudaf~aEN","text_ar":"مُدَفَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b9-  [In several exs. here following, the verb resembles"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AndfE","text_ar":"اندفع"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosahu","text_ar":"نَفْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the like, being understood after it.] ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa AlmaA='u","text_ar":"دَفَعَ المَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water poured out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth, as though it impelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"propelled, itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA: [where it is followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@noSab~a","text_ar":"وَا@نْصَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an explicative adjunct:]) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayolu","text_ar":"السَّيْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":891},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"torrent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (ISh.) [See also 6.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"دَفَعَ الوَادِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlmaA='i","text_ar":"بِالمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The valley poured with water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$k","text_ar":"حشك"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa fiY Eadowihi","text_ar":"دَفَعَ فِى عَدْوِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pushed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pressed, on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forward, as though he impelled himself, in his running"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gwr","text_ar":"غور"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.) [See also 7.] ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa Alqawomu","text_ar":"دَفَعَ القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men, came at once."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa A_ilaY","text_ar":"دَفَعَ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmakaAni","text_ar":"المَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dufiEa A_ilayohi","text_ar":"دُفِعَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) in the pass. form, (Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He reached,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to, the place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA TariyqN yadofaEu","text_ar":"هٰذَا طَرِيقٌ يَدْفَعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY makaAni ka*aA","text_ar":"اـِلَى مَكَانِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a road which reaches to such a place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa mino EarafaAtK","text_ar":"دَفَعَ مِنْ عَرَفَاتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He commenced the journey from 'Arafát, and impelled and removed himself thence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impelled his she-camel, and urged her to go."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu Eani AlmawoDiEi","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ عَنِ المَوْضِعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I removed, went, went away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeyed, from the place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [See again 7.] ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEa","text_ar":"دَفَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF.) ―         -b16-  When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafoEN","text_ar":"دَفْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", it [generally, but not always, as has been shown above,] has the meaning of the act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Giving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delivering;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur [iv. 5],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@dofaEuwA A_ilayohimo A^amowaAlahumo","text_ar":"فَا@دْفَعُوا اـِلَيْهِمْ اَمْوَالَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then give ye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deliver ye, to them their property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (B.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaYY fulaAnK $ayoy^FA","text_ar":"اـِلَىى فُلَانٍ شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delivered, to such a one a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu AlwadiyEapa A_ilaY SaAHibihaA","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ الوَدِيعَةَ اـِلَى صَاحِبِهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I restored the deposit to its owner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu lahu qiToEapF mina AlmaAli","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ لَهُ قِطْعَةً مِنَ المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him a part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, of the property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zEb","text_ar":"زعب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the like is said in that art. in the K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEahu","text_ar":"دَفَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTaAhu","text_ar":"اَعْطَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Er-Rághib, MF.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n12720","headword_ar":"دَفْعَةٌ","root":"dfE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single impulsion; a push, a thrust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single act of driving;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to remove a thing from its place; a single propulsion; a single repulsion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K, * TA:) [it is an inf. n. of un. of 1 in all its senses; and thus,] it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single act of pouring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.:] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEaAtN","text_ar":"دَفَعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEahu dafoEapF","text_ar":"دَفَعَهُ دَفْعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He impelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"once"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a single impulsion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TK.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu mina AlA_inaA='i dafoEapF","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ مِنَ الاـِنَا=ءِ دَفْعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I poured forth from the vessel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single pouring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  [As an inf. n. of un. of 1,] it also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A coming of the collective body of a people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party of men, to a place at once."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heat, a single course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one unintermitted act,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of running, or the like.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12721","headword_ar":"دُفْعَةٌ","root":"dfE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quantity that pours forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out, at once,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a skin, or vessel: (Lth, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a quantity poured forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out, at once,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with vehemence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"being] syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dufoqapN","text_ar":"دُفْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IF, S, Msb, K, [in the CK with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) of rain, [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a shower, fall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"storm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity that falls without intermission,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (IF, S, Msb, K,) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gush"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of blood, (IF, Msb,) &c.: (IF, S, Msb:) it is also [used as signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tide"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a valley, (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"THm","text_ar":"طحم"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rush,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a torrent, (S and K in that art.,) and [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rush,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irruption,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a troop of horses or horsemen, (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dlq","text_ar":"دلق"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,) and [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irruption,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"invasion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of night: (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"THm","text_ar":"طحم"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dufaEN","text_ar":"دُفَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dufaEaAtN","text_ar":"دُفَعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dufuEaAtN","text_ar":"دُفُعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dufoEaAtN","text_ar":"دُفْعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiYafiY AlA_inaA='i dufoEapN","text_ar":"بَقِىَفِى الاـِنَا=ءِ دُفْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There remained in the vessel as much as one pours out at once."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, that is given,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of property. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zEb","text_ar":"زعب"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","K","Msb","IF","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}